avelers × $44)\",\n          \"category\": \"insurance\",\n          \"amount\": 88,\n          \"currency\": \"USD\",\n          \"paid\": false,\n          \"paid_amount\": 0,\n          \"notes\": \"Zanzibar Insurance Corporation — mandatory.\",\n          \"origin\": \"trip-costs.xlsx\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"id\": \"e028a5a6-a67d-4fe9-8655-ba2c5d153ba0\",\n          \"item\": \"Ngorongoro Conservation Area entry permit (2 pax × $70.80)\",\n          \"category\": \"park fees\",\n          \"amount\": 141.6,\n          \"currency\": \"USD\",\n          \"paid\": false,\n          \"paid_amount\": 0,\n          \"notes\": \"Non-EA adult, 1 day. Valid for 24h single entry.\",\n          \"origin\": \"trip-costs.xlsx\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"id\": \"af59c17e-9e29-4d9a-9e36-46c73b324c0b\",\n          \"item\": \"Ngorongoro crater service fee (2 pax × $70.80)\",\n          \"category\": \"park fees\",\n          \"amount\": 141.6,\n          \"currency\": \"USD\",\n          \"paid\": false,\n          \"paid_amount\": 0,\n          \"notes\": \"Non-EA adult. Crater descent gates close 16:00; exit by 18:00.\",\n          \"origin\": \"trip-costs.xlsx\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"id\": \"ab76d4ae-9b8b-4471-9293-29e5220cac01\",\n          \"item\": \"Ngorongoro crater vehicle descent fee (per vehicle/trip)\",\n          \"category\": \"park fees\",\n          \"amount\": 295,\n          \"currency\": \"USD\",\n          \"paid\": false,\n          \"paid_amount\": 0,\n          \"notes\": \"Non-EA registered vehicle. Tare weight up to 2000kg = $295; 2001-3000kg = $354 (check vehicle).\",\n          \"origin\": \"trip-costs.xlsx\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"id\": \"045d4f53-2596-45ce-91ba-b7eaa6cc9652\",\n          \"item\": \"Tarangire NP entrance (2 pax × $59, peak season)\",\n          \"category\": \"park fees\",\n          \"amount\": 118,\n          \"currency\": \"USD\",\n          \"paid\": false,\n          \"paid_amount\": 0,\n          \"notes\": \"Peak season (August).\",\n          \"origin\": \"trip-costs.xlsx\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"id\": \"3c73397e-de04-4224-b823-fa5ff18d630e\",\n          \"item\": \"Lake Manyara NP entrance (2 pax × $59, peak season)\",\n          \"category\": \"park fees\",\n          \"amount\": 118,\n          \"currency\": \"USD\",\n          \"paid\": false,\n          \"paid_amount\": 0,\n          \"notes\": \"Peak season (August).\",\n          \"origin\": \"trip-costs.xlsx\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"id\": \"119db0eb-9320-4284-9b0b-6ba99040a18f\",\n          \"item\": \"Cairo arrival stopover — Eileen Hotel, Aug 3-5\",\n          \"category\": \"lodging\",\n          \"amount\": 102,\n          \"currency\": \"USD\",\n          \"paid\": false,\n          \"paid_amount\": 0,\n          \"notes\": \"2 nights. Near Tahrir Square/Nile Corniche.\",\n          \"origin\": \"trip-costs.xlsx\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"id\": \"8f3282cb-4356-48ff-894d-855f98ea72a4\",\n          \"item\": \"Arusha pre-safari — Serengeti Villa, Aug 5-7\",\n          \"category\": \"lodging\",\n          \"amount\": 62,\n          \"currency\": \"USD\",\n          \"paid\": false,\n          \"paid_amount\": 0,\n          \"notes\": \"2 nights. Ph: +255 757 757 928.\",\n          \"origin\": \"trip-costs.xlsx\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"id\": \"10146837-c908-4b06-9f81-6741dde778d5\",\n          \"item\": \"Arusha post-safari — Kutoka Lodge, Aug 9-11\",\n          \"category\": \"lodging\",\n          \"amount\": 96,\n          \"currency\": \"USD\",\n          \"paid\": false,\n          \"paid_amount\": 0,\n          \"notes\": \"2 nights.\",\n          \"origin\": \"trip-costs.xlsx\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"id\": \"41b46386-dae8-4bca-a1d4-fd670cd74c4c\",\n          \"item\": \"Zanzibar Stone Town — Treasures of Zanzibar House, Aug 11-13\",\n          \"category\": \"lodging\",\n          \"amount\": 100,\n          \"currency\": \"USD\",\n          \"paid\": false,\n          \"paid_amount\": 0,\n          \"notes\": \"2 nights. Stone Town.\",\n          \"origin\": \"trip-costs.xlsx\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"id\": \"eb3d3b1e-4580-4996-b6fa-cbd7efc3ad93\",\n          \"item\": \"Zanzibar beach — Ayla Beach House, Kiwengwa, Aug 13-17\",\n          \"category\": \"lodging\",\n          \"amount\": 304,\n          \"currency\": \"USD\",\n          \"paid\": false,\n          \"paid_amount\": 0,\n          \"notes\": \"4 nights. North coast (Nungwi area) — best swimming conditions.\",\n          \"origin\": \"trip-costs.xlsx\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"id\": \"803b6514-4ac7-4566-8870-dff6d5399067\",\n          \"item\": \"Dar es Salaam — Sunny Shore B&B, Aug 17-19\",\n          \"category\": \"lodging\",\n          \"amount\": 200,\n          \"currency\": \"USD\",\n          \"paid\": false,\n          \"paid_amount\": 0,\n          \"notes\": \"2 nights.\",\n          \"origin\": \"trip-costs.xlsx\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"id\": \"61277aff-5d51-4719-b503-2b89ad9d76f0\",\n          \"item\": \"Cairo departure stopover — Ramses Hilton, Aug 19-20\",\n          \"category\": \"lodging\",\n          \"amount\": 87,\n          \"currency\": \"USD\",\n          \"paid\": false,\n          \"paid_amount\": 0,\n          \"notes\": \"1 night.\",\n          \"origin\": \"trip-costs.xlsx\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"journal_entries\": [\n        {\n          \"id\": \"b45e2524-f531-44d0-b11b-23d466160c45\",\n          \"date\": \"Aug 3-5\",\n          \"title\": \"Cairo Arrival Stopover\",\n          \"body\": \"Arrive Cairo Aug 3 (Aegean A3932, 06:55–08:50, ref ZZJQUU). Staying at Eileen Hotel near Tahrir Square/Nile Corniche. Sightseeing plan: Grand Egyptian Museum and Pyramids of Giza. Fly out Aug 4 at 22:40 on EgyptAir to Dar es Salaam (arrive 04:20+1). Late checkout Aug 5 not needed for sleep.\",\n          \"category\": \"journal\",\n          \"location\": \"Cairo, Egypt\",\n          \"contacts\": \"Eileen Hotel: +20 15 56434043, info@eileenhotel.com, 21 Youssef El-Gendy St, Abdeen, Downtown Cairo\",\n          \"origin\": \"tanzaniamemories.md\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"id\": \"6afcfb6b-5d73-47c8-a223-f6ab335b5e2f\",\n          \"date\": \"Aug 5\",\n          \"title\": \"Transit Day — Cairo → Dar → Arusha\",\n          \"body\": \"EgyptAir CAI→DAR lands 04:20. Connect to Precision Air TC144 DAR→ARK, 10:50–12:00. Arrive Arusha midday. Stay: Serengeti Villa (+255 757 757 928), Aug 5-7.\",\n          \"category\": \"journal\",\n          \"location\": \"Dar es Salaam → Arusha, Tanzania\",\n          \"contacts\": \"Serengeti Villa: +255 757 757 928\",\n          \"origin\": \"tanzaniamemories.md\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"id\": \"5d05b0e7-fa26-4af1-b213-d10c609762e2\",\n          \"date\": \"Aug 5-7\",\n          \"title\": \"Arusha Pre-Safari\",\n          \"body\": \"Two nights at Serengeti Villa, Arusha. Prep for safari. Tanzania e-visa ($50/person) must be done online at visa.immigration.go.tz — visa-on-arrival no longer available. Zanzibar also requires separate mandatory travel insurance from ZIC.\",\n          \"category\": \"journal\",\n          \"location\": \"Arusha, Tanzania\",\n          \"contacts\": \"\",\n          \"origin\": \"tanzaniamemories.md\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"id\": \"1bbaac45-ae76-4db7-b85e-966a443ff13f\",\n          \"date\": \"Aug 7-9\",\n          \"title\": \"Suricata Safaris — 3-Day Group Camping Safari\",\n          \"body\": \"Safari with Suricata Safaris Ltd. Day 1: Tarangire National Park (Twiga Camp Site, FB). Day 2: Lake Manyara National Park (Twiga Camp Site, FB). Day 3: Ngorongoro Crater (overnight at Jevas Hotel, HB). Safari package: $1,200 total for 2 pax. $240 deposit (20%) paid. $960 balance due on arrival in cash (post-2009 USD notes) or online via Pesapal (+5% surcharge): payments.pesapal.com/suricatasafaris. Contact: Richard, +255 763 222 293, info@suricatasafaris.com.\",\n          \"category\": \"journal\",\n          \"location\": \"Tarangire → Lake Manyara → Ngorongoro Crater, Tanzania\",\n          \"contacts\": \"Richard (Suricata Safaris): +255 763 222 293, info@suricatasafaris.com\",\n          \"origin\": \"tanzaniamemories.md\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"id\": \"9790321e-5e85-45ca-b64e-8989cb934013\",\n          \"date\": \"Aug 9\",\n          \"title\": \"Ngorongoro Crater Day — One of the Best Days of the Trip\",\n          \"body\": \"Driver guide: Emmanuel (not Richard) — excellent, pointed out wildlife before it was visible. Bought 2 beaded bracelets from a Maasai lady at the crater rim for Athina Mari — ~$20-25 USD / ~TZS 35,000, exact amount uncertain. Emmanuel mentioned an extra ranger tip at the gate: ~TZS 5,000 cash, separate from park fees — nobody told us beforehand. Described as one of the best days of the trip. Park fees for the day: entry permit $70.80/person, crater service fee $70.80/person, vehicle descent fee $295 (up to 2000kg). Ngorongoro nights are cold — warm layers needed.\",\n          \"category\": \"journal\",\n          \"location\": \"Ngorongoro Crater, Tanzania\",\n          \"contacts\": \"Emmanuel (driver guide)\",\n          \"origin\": \"voice memo transcription\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"id\": \"c2ab3b17-39b2-496f-9d25-a03f56f0d3e0\",\n          \"date\": \"Aug 9-11\",\n          \"title\": \"Arusha Post-Safari — Kutoka Lodge\",\n          \"body\": \"Two nights at Kutoka Lodge, Arusha. Rest after safari. Next: fly to Zanzibar Aug 11 (Precision Air TC145, 12:40–13:40). Precision Air has luggage restrictions favoring soft bags.\",\n          \"category\": \"journal\",\n          \"location\": \"Arusha, Tanzania\",\n          \"contacts\": \"\",\n          \"origin\": \"tanzaniamemories.md\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"id\": \"0462bda7-83f8-4502-813b-f240e8cf7f9f\",\n          \"date\": \"Aug 11-13\",\n          \"title\": \"Zanzibar — Stone Town\",\n          \"body\": \"Fly ARK→ZNZ Aug 11 (Precision Air TC145, 12:40–13:40). Stay: Treasures of Zanzibar House, 2 nights. Explore Stone Town.\",\n          \"category\": \"journal\",\n          \"location\": \"Stone Town, Zanzibar\",\n          \"contacts\": \"\",\n          \"origin\": \"tanzaniamemories.md\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"id\": \"23ce6a6f-7a8d-4e9b-9867-00013f0de3d3\",\n          \"date\": \"Aug 13-17\",\n          \"title\": \"Zanzibar — Beach (Kiwengwa)\",\n          \"body\": \"Stay: Ayla Beach House, Kiwengwa, 4 nights. North coast (Nungwi area) offers more consistent swimming conditions vs. east/south where low tide limits access. Zanzibar local driving permit required (~$15, valid up to 3 months). Vasilis holds an IDP — most rental companies arrange the local permit with license photo 24+ hours before. Police checkpoints are frequent; carry both IDP and local permit (screenshot acceptable).\",\n          \"category\": \"journal\",\n          \"location\": \"Kiwengwa, Zanzibar\",\n          \"contacts\": \"\",\n          \"origin\": \"tanzaniamemories.md\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"id\": \"4a7a1251-19ee-4224-aa75-0576adebdf1a\",\n          \"date\": \"Aug 15\",\n          \"title\": \"The Rock Restaurant Dinner\",\n          \"body\": \"The Rock Restaurant, Zanzibar. Aug 15, 18:00–20:00 sitting. 2 adults. 2x Tropical Passion Fruit Cheesecake included. Fully paid ($46). Outdoor seating requested for sunset/star views. Contact: +255 776 591 360 / +255 763 070 658, booking@therockrestaurantzanzibar.com.\",\n          \"category\": \"journal\",\n          \"location\": \"The Rock Restaurant, Zanzibar\",\n          \"contacts\": \"+255 776 591 360 / +255 763 070 658, booking@therockrestaurantzanzibar.com\",\n          \"origin\": \"tanzaniamemories.md\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"id\": \"16e600fd-51f0-4294-903c-ddb1c33b5559\",\n          \"date\": \"Aug 17-19\",\n          \"title\": \"Dar es Salaam\",\n          \"body\": \"Arrive by ferry from Zanzibar. Stay: Sunny Shore B&B, 2 nights. Interest in city exploration: Kivukoni Fish Market, Kariakoo Market, National Museum, Coco Beach, Bongoyo Island.\",\n          \"category\": \"journal\",\n          \"location\": \"Dar es Salaam, Tanzania\",\n          \"contacts\": \"\",\n          \"origin\": \"tanzaniamemories.md\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"id\": \"a7484914-b616-4112-9580-1ecd9cb65030\",\n          \"date\": \"Aug 19-20\",\n          \"title\": \"Cairo Departure Stopover\",\n          \"body\": \"EgyptAir DAR→CAI, 05:20–11:05. Stay: Ramses Hilton, 1 night. Sightseeing: Islamic Cairo, the Citadel, Khan el-Khalili bazaar, Coptic Cairo. Taxi needed between Citadel and Coptic Cairo. Fly home Aug 20: Aegean A3935 CAI→ATH, 19:55–22:00, ref ZZL22S.\",\n          \"category\": \"journal\",\n          \"location\": \"Cairo, Egypt\",\n          \"contacts\": \"Ramses Hilton, Cairo\",\n          \"origin\": \"tanzaniamemories.md\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"id\": \"1b9c173f-5cc3-4348-8668-489496c6a2cf\",\n          \"date\": \"Aug 3-20\",\n          \"title\": \"Trip Summary & Key Learnings\",\n          \"body\": \"Full trip: Aug 3-20, 2026. Vasileios Kefallinos + Athina Mari. Cairo → Arusha → Tanzania safari circuit → Zanzibar → Dar es Salaam. Total flights: ~€2,707 (6 legs). Total lodging (excl. safari): ~$951. Safari: $1,200. Key tips: EgyptAir operates Cairo↔Dar — confirmed. Tanzania e-visa mandatory online ($50/person). Egypt e-visa multiple-entry ($65), printed copy mandatory. Ngorongoro nights are cold. Zanzibar: north coast best for swimming. Precision Air: soft bags preferred. August is peak safari season — ideal for Great Wildebeest Migration. Vasilis prefers simple, concise output (bullet lists over tables).\",\n          \"category\": \"note\",\n          \"location\": \"Multi-city\",\n          \"contacts\": \"\",\n          \"origin\": \"tanzaniamemories.md\"\n        }