Citadel and Coptic Cairo. Fly home Aug 20: Aegean A3935 CAI→ATH, 19:55–22:00, ref ZZL22S.\",\n/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/automation/instances/scenario-campaign/rounds/4/06-tanzania/attempt-1/step-02.json:1256:          \"location\": \"Cairo, Egypt\",\n/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/automation/instances/scenario-campaign/rounds/4/06-tanzania/attempt-1/step-02.json:1257:          \"contacts\": \"Ramses Hilton, Cairo\",\n/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/automation/instances/scenario-campaign/rounds/4/06-tanzania/attempt-1/step-02.json:1264:          \"body\": \"Full trip: Aug 3-20, 2026. Vasileios Kefallinos + Athina Mari. Cairo → Arusha → Tanzania safari circuit → Zanzibar → Dar es Salaam. Total flights: ~€2,707 (6 legs). Total lodging (excl. safari): ~$951. Safari: $1,200. Key tips: EgyptAir operates Cairo↔Dar — confirmed. Tanzania e-visa mandatory online ($50/person). Egypt e-visa multiple-entry ($65), printed copy mandatory. Ngorongoro nights are cold. Zanzibar: north coast best for swimming. Precision Air: soft bags preferred. August is peak safari season — ideal for Great Wildebeest Migration. Vasilis prefers simple, concise output (bullet lists over tables).\",","stderr":"","interrupted":false,"isImage":false,"noOutputExpected":false}}
