{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_gDkUT0tz4mZlnU3iGcXNCLwD","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t---\n2\tid: build\n3\toutput:\n4\t  spaceKey: string\n5\t  agentSlug: string\n6\t  actionId: string\n7\t  query: string\n8\t  ok: boolean\n9\t  errors: string\n10\tdependsOn: [research]\n11\tgoal: true\n12\trole: general\n13\tfunctions: []\n14\tcanDelegateTo:\n15\t  - system-architect/architect#synthesize_and_run\n16\t---\n17\t\n18\tHand the user's `request` (a seed variable in scope) plus the upstream research to the architect,\n19\twhich designs, scaffolds, validates, and registers the new specialist agent. `research` is the\n20\tupstream output `{ report }` — the report may be `{}` (empty) when research was unavailable;\n21\tdelegate ANYWAY, the architect's build tolerates thin research. This task ALWAYS runs. Emit:\n22\t\n23\tconst t = await delegate('system-architect', 'architect', 'synthesize_and_run', { query: String(request), context: { topic: String(request), goal: String(request), research: (research && research.report) ? research.report : {} } });\n24\t\n25\t(If `research` is not in scope at all — the optional research task was skipped — pass\n26\t`research: {}` in `context` instead.)\n27\t\n28\t`t` is the architect's envelope `{ ok, degraded, data }`; `t.data` is the build result\n29\t({ spaceKey, agentSlug, actionId, query, ok, errors }). Package it field-for-field — on a\n30\tmissing/failed result, resolve empty coordinates with `ok: false` and the error in `errors`\n31\t(never fabricate coordinates). Emit:\n32\t\n33\tconst built = (t && t.data) ? t.data : { spaceKey: \"\", agentSlug: \"\", actionId: \"\", query: \"\", ok: false, errors: \"the architect returned no result\" };\n34\t\n35\tcurrentTask.resolve({ spaceKey: String(built.spaceKey || \"\"), agentSlug: String(built.agentSlug || \"\"), actionId: String(built.actionId || \"\"), query: String(built.query || request), ok: !!(t && t.ok === true && built.ok === true), errors: String(built.errors || \"\") });\n36\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"call_tAtAZq2TO7AmfB0HW38CuDLZ","session_id":"2142c1ae-f65f-4763-943d-8eaf39a5f62b","uuid":"8a85a836-a6e1-4634-87b9-cfc1bc9a2baa","timestamp":"2026-07-15T18:22:18.144Z","subagent_type":"Explore","task_description":"Trace Tanzania build routing"}
