{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_Yq2g96NahlAt5WDPEmF6bGZF","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t---\n2\tinput:\n3\t  topic: string\n4\t  goal: string\n5\t  research: string\n6\t---\n7\t\n8\tBuild a brand-new specialist agent (a \"space\") for the user's request, ONE FILE AT A TIME,\n9\tthen validate and register it so it can be run. The seed gives `topic` (the user's request,\n10\tverbatim), `goal` (what the new agent should do), and `research` — a JSON string of a cited\n11\tdeep-research report ({ topic, executive_summary, findings:[{heading,detail}], conclusion,\n12\tsources:[{title,url}] }) used to write VALIDATED, SOURCED knowledge. The host runs the steps\n13\tbelow in order and fans the per-field / per-function steps out for you — each writes one piece.\n14\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"call_tAtAZq2TO7AmfB0HW38CuDLZ","session_id":"2142c1ae-f65f-4763-943d-8eaf39a5f62b","uuid":"67226c13-9390-45c7-80b2-0beb813f9c4b","timestamp":"2026-07-15T18:24:31.631Z","subagent_type":"Explore","task_description":"Trace Tanzania build routing"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_LgWPrkRxDP7BJ37d0kj4MRy1","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t---\n2\tid: design\n3\toutput:\n4\t  slug: string\n5\t  goal: string\n6\t  actionId: string\n7\t  fields: array\n8\t  functions: array\n9\tdependsOn: []\n10\trole: explore\n11\tfunctions: []\n12\t---\n13\t\n14\tDesign the specialist agent from the seed (`topic`, `goal`). This is a PLANNING step: you have no\n15\tfile or research tools here — just reason from the seed, build the plan object, and resolve it.\n16\t\n17\tSubstitute REAL values for every `<…>` below (a small model copying `<…>` verbatim is the #1\n18\tfailure — never leave a placeholder in the resolved values):\n19\t\n20\tconst slug = \"<short-lowercase-slug derived from the topic, e.g. cocktail-advisor>\";\n21\t// KNOWLEDGE FIELDS the agent needs. Each: { domain, field, aspects } where `aspects` is 2-4\n22\t// distinct sub-topic slugs (NOT \"overview\"). Add as many fields as the domain genuinely needs.\n23\tconst fields = [\n24\t  { domain: \"<domain_slug>\", field: \"<field_slug>\", aspects: [\"<aspect_a>\", \"<aspect_b>\"] }\n25\t];\n26\t// Deterministic FUNCTIONS the agent needs (math / scoring / lookup). Often none.\n27\t// ANNOTATE THE TYPE — keep the annotation below even when the array is empty. An empty array\n28\t// literal declared with no type annotation does not typecheck once it is passed on: the checker\n29\t// cannot infer an element type and fails with \"implicitly has an 'any[]' type\". Every rewrite from\n30\t// there is a dead end too (redeclaring the name, or assigning to a const, are both errors).\n31\tconst functions: Array<{ name: string; purpose: string }> = [];   // e.g. [{ name: \"scoreMatch\", purpose: \"score a drink against a mood (0-10)\" }]\n32\tconst actionId = \"answer\";   // the single action the agent will expose\n33\tconst goal = \"<one-sentence refined goal for the agent>\";\n34\tcurrentTask.resolve({ slug, goal, actionId, fields, functions });\n35\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"call_tAtAZq2TO7AmfB0HW38CuDLZ","session_id":"2142c1ae-f65f-4763-943d-8eaf39a5f62b","uuid":"83f2da69-d9c3-41cf-a392-e4050c72a85b","timestamp":"2026-07-15T18:24:31.632Z","subagent_type":"Explore","task_description":"Trace Tanzania build routing"}
