{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_AYQbshNxb133TPOXXhJBsaKO","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t---\n2\tid: build_field\n3\toutput:\n4\t  domain: string\n5\t  field: string\n6\t  aspect: string\n7\t  ok: boolean\n8\tdependsOn: [design]\n9\tforEach: design.fields\n10\toptional: true\n11\trole: general\n12\tfunctions:\n13\t  - writeKnowledgeIndex\n14\t  - writeKnowledgeOption\n15\t---\n16\t\n17\tWrite ONE knowledge field's files, grounded in the deep-research report (the validated, sourced\n18\tknowledge is already in the `research` seed; you have only the knowledge-writing tools). Your field is in `item` =\n19\t{ domain, field, aspects }; the space slug is `design.slug`. Emit, in order:\n20\t\n21\tconst f = item;\n22\tconst report = (() => { try { return JSON.parse(research); } catch { return { findings: [], sources: [] }; } })();\n23\t// Pull the report findings + source URLs relevant to this field; cite real sources, never fabricate.\n24\tconst findings = Array.isArray(report.findings) ? report.findings : [];\n25\tconst srcUrl = (Array.isArray(report.sources) && report.sources[0]) ? report.sources[0].url : \"the research report\";\n26\t// index.md body = the field OVERVIEW: a short paragraph introducing EACH aspect, drawn from `findings`.\n27\twriteKnowledgeIndex(design.slug, f.domain, f.field, { variable: f.field + \"Knowledge\", description: \"<overview paragraph introducing every aspect, grounded in the report>\" });\n28\t// One option file per aspect (>=2), each a distinct sub-topic grounded in `findings`, with a Source line.\n29\twriteKnowledgeOption(design.slug, f.domain, f.field, f.aspects[0], \"# \" + f.aspects[0] + \"\\n\\n<content grounded in the report>\\n\\nSource: \" + srcUrl);\n30\twriteKnowledgeOption(design.slug, f.domain, f.field, f.aspects[1], \"# \" + f.aspects[1] + \"\\n\\n<content grounded in the report>\");\n31\tcurrentTask.resolve({ domain: f.domain, field: f.field, aspect: f.aspects[0], ok: true });\n32\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"call_tAtAZq2TO7AmfB0HW38CuDLZ","session_id":"2142c1ae-f65f-4763-943d-8eaf39a5f62b","uuid":"67afc4ab-cc30-48b1-982f-af9eb4b53aae","timestamp":"2026-07-15T18:24:31.641Z","subagent_type":"Explore","task_description":"Trace Tanzania build routing"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_aquKSIqVXN70V3SuBOBzhDaf","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t---\n2\ttitle: App Architect\n3\tknowledge:\n4\t  - app_building/model\n5\tfunctions: []\n6\tcomponents: []\n7\tcapabilities:\n8\t  - project:manage\n9\t  - db:schema\n10\t  - db:read\n11\t  - pages:write\n12\t  - api:write\n13\t  - hooks:write\n14\tdefaultAction: build_app\n15\tactions:\n16\t  - id: build_app\n17\t    label: Build App\n18\t    description: Turn a natural-language app request into a working project — database schemas, typed API handlers, React pages, and hooks — built file-by-file.\n19\t    tasklist: build_app\n20\tcanDelegateTo:\n21\t  - system-appbuilder/data-modeler\n22\t  - system-appbuilder/page-builder\n23\t  - system-appbuilder/api-author\n24\t  - system-appbuilder/automator\n25\t  - system-research/researcher\n26\t---\n27\t\n28\tYou build a complete application from a natural-language request. The build is a short fixed\n29\tprogram: run the `build_app` tasklist and let the HOST drive the file-by-file build (design →\n30\tcreate project → tables → API → pages → hooks → finalize). Do NOT try to design or write the app\n31\tfiles here at the top level — that heavy lifting happens INSIDE the tasklist, one file per step.\n32\t\n33\tEmit TWO statements across two turns.\n34\t\n35\t```typescript\n36\t// Turn 1 — run the build pipeline, seeded with the user's request (verbatim).\n37\t// t = { ok, degraded, data } — branch on t.ok; the build summary is t.data.\n38\tconst t = await tasklist('build_app', { request: query });\n39\t```\n40\t```typescript\n41\t// Turn 2 — a VARIABLES block means MID-PROGRAM, not done. Report what was built.\n42\tconst built = t.data as { appId: string; tables: unknown[]; pages: unknown[]; endpoints: unknown[]; hooks: unknown[] };\n43\tdisplay(t.ok\n44\t  ? 'Built app \"' + built.appId + '\": ' + built.tables.length + ' table(s), ' + built.endpoints.length + ' endpoint(s), ' + built.pages.length + ' page(s), ' + built.hooks.length + ' hook(s).'\n45\t  : 'The app build did not complete: ' + (t.reason ?? 'unknown'));\n46\t```\n47\t\n48\t## Rules\n49\t\n50\t- A value-yielding `await tasklist(...)` PAUSES you; the host runs the whole pipeline and resumes\n51\t  you next turn with the result — that means CONTINUE (emit Turn 2), not done.\n52\t- When a specialized sub-part needs isolation you MAY delegate one slice to a specialist\n53\t  (`data-modeler`, `page-builder`, `api-author`, `automator`), but the default path is the\n54\t  `build_app` tasklist, which already runs every step under your own authoring capabilities.\n55\t- Never fabricate a table/endpoint/page you did not design. Pages use design tokens only.\n56\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"call_tAtAZq2TO7AmfB0HW38CuDLZ","session_id":"2142c1ae-f65f-4763-943d-8eaf39a5f62b","uuid":"ed62e55c-1fc6-4b76-88c3-fc2bd8f5034d","timestamp":"2026-07-15T18:24:31.642Z","subagent_type":"Explore","task_description":"Trace Tanzania build routing"}
