wait loadKnowledge(...bf.aspect...)\") : \"\";\n```\n\n`/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/sdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/system-architect/tasklists/synthesize_and_run/05-write_tasks.md:22-28`\n\nThus the Zanzibar agent loads only `courtyards.md`, not its `zanzibar/trip-context` knowledge. The replay records `covered:false`, then `research_and_store`, then `webSearch` at:\n\n`/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/sdk/org/scenarios/harness/.state/local-server/serve.log:7526-7604`\n\nThe app state contains tables/APIs but only `_layout.tsx`, no `index` page:\n\n`/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/sdk/org/scenarios/harness/.state/local-server/pod-root/.lmthing/tanzania-trip/pages/`\n\nThe log confirms the automator returned undefined and the retry stopped at assessment/scope errors (`serve.log:8434-8622`).\n\n### 3. Smallest L1 change\n\nAdd directly after THING’s “distinct PARTS” rule:\n\n> For an agreed build from supplied material, create one evidence contract before delegating: retain every attachment ID and image/audio fact; partition every distinct itinerary leg/topic into exactly one topical space, never an overview substitute; seed each space only with its complete supplied facts and prohibit research during the build; pass all source IDs and extracted non-readable facts to the automator; report completion only after a seeded index/dashboard renders real rows.\n\n**Principle:** Accepted builds carry a complete, partitioned source-evidence contract; research fills only proven gaps, and “done” means a rendered, usable app—not tables alone."}],"model":"gpt-5.6-terra","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":"call_tAtAZq2TO7AmfB0HW38CuDLZ","session_id":"2142c1ae-f65f-4763-943d-8eaf39a5f62b","uuid":"f79c9779-e99b-41e3-9ed3-1eca946c4805","subagent_type":"Explore","task_description":"Trace Tanzania build routing"}
