{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_dbUsv8hx9tmoTTFPAgHWwRYx","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t---\n2\tid: write_agent\n3\toutput:\n4\t  ok: boolean\n5\t  agentSlug: string\n6\tdependsOn: [design, build_field, build_function]\n7\trole: general\n8\tfunctions:\n9\t  - writeAgentFile\n10\t---\n11\t\n12\tWrite the agent header — charter.md + instruct.md — with writeAgentFile. The slug is\n13\t`design.slug`. `build_field` is the array of knowledge fields actually written\n14\t({ domain, field, aspect, ok }); `build_function` is the array of functions written\n15\t({ name, ok }). DERIVE every ref from what was actually written — never invent a ref.\n16\t\n17\tEvery synthesized agent gets `capabilities: ['knowledge:write']` so that when a question falls\n18\tOUTSIDE its static knowledge it can research the answer and PERSIST it (its `research_and_store`\n19\taction), instead of guessing — the next time that question is free. Give the agent BOTH actions: its\n20\tnormal `answer` action, and `research_and_store`. Its top-level prompt runs `answer` first, and only\n21\tif the knowledge did not cover the question does it fall back to researching and storing. Emit:\n22\t\n23\tconst kfields = Array.isArray(build_field) ? build_field.filter((x: { ok: boolean }) => x.ok) : [];\n24\tconst knowledgeRefs = kfields.map((x: { domain: string; field: string }) => x.domain + \"/\" + x.field);\n25\tconst fnNames = (Array.isArray(build_function) ? build_function.filter((x: { ok: boolean }) => x.ok) : []).map((x: { name: string }) => x.name);\n26\tconst w = writeAgentFile(design.slug, {\n27\t  agentSlug: design.slug,\n28\t  agentTitle: \"<Title Case name>\",\n29\t  // charter = fork-safe identity: 2-3 sentences on WHO the agent is + its domain + one guardrail.\n30\t  // No ask/delegate/UI/routing instructions here.\n31\t  charter: \"<2-3 sentence identity + domain + a 'never fabricate' guardrail>\",\n32\t  // systemPrompt = top-level orchestration: answer from knowledge; on a gap, research + store, then answer.\n33\t  systemPrompt: \"You answer the user's request (in `query`) about <domain>. FIRST run your answer tasklist: const a = await tasklist('\" + design.actionId + \"', { query }); a is { ok, degraded, data }. If a.data.covered is true, display a.data.answer + a.data.sources next turn. If a.data.covered is FALSE, your static knowledge did not cover it — research and SAVE it, then answer: const s = await tasklist('research_and_store', { query, domain: '<primary knowledge domain>', field: '<primary field>' }); display s.data.answer + s.data.sources. Never guess a fact your knowledge lacks — that is exactly what research_and_store is for.\",\n34\t  knowledge: knowledgeRefs,\n35\t  functions: fnNames,\n36\t  capabilities: [\"knowledge:write\"],\n37\t  actions: [\n38\t    { id: design.actionId, label: \"<Label>\", description: \"<what the action does>\", tasklist: design.actionId },\n39\t    { id: \"research_and_store\", label: \"Research and store\", description: \"Research a question the static knowledge does not cover and save the finding into this space's knowledge.\", tasklist: \"research_and_store\" },\n40\t  ],\n41\t  defaultAction: design.actionId,\n42\t});\n43\tcurrentTask.resolve({ ok: w.ok, agentSlug: design.slug });\n44\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"2142c1ae-f65f-4763-943d-8eaf39a5f62b","uuid":"37e51a64-9e74-413e-8321-add927f10aec","timestamp":"2026-07-15T18:33:28.666Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/sdk/org/libs/core/system-spaces/system-architect/tasklists/synthesize_and_run/04-write_agent.md","content":"---\nid: write_agent\noutput:\n  ok: boolean\n  agentSlug: string\ndependsOn: [design, build_field, build_function]\nrole: general\nfunctions:\n  - writeAgentFile\n---\n\nWrite the agent header — charter.md + instruct.md — with writeAgentFile. The slug is\n`design.slug`. `build_field` is the array of knowledge fields actually written\n({ domain, field, aspect, ok }); `build_function` is the array of functions written\n({ name, ok }). DERIVE every ref from what was actually written — never invent a ref.\n\nEvery synthesized agent gets `capabilities: ['knowledge:write']` so that when a question falls\nOUTSIDE its static knowledge it can research the answer and PERSIST it (its `research_and_store`\naction), instead of guessing — the next time that question is free. Give the agent BOTH actions: its\nnormal `answer` action, and `research_and_store`. Its top-level prompt runs `answer` first, and only\nif the knowledge did not cover the question does it fall back to researching and storing. Emit:\n\nconst kfields = Array.isArray(build_field) ? build_field.filter((x: { ok: boolean }) => x.ok) : [];\nconst knowledgeRefs = kfields.map((x: { domain: string; field: string }) => x.domain + \"/\" + x.field);\nconst fnNames = (Array.isArray(build_function) ? build_function.filter((x: { ok: boolean }) => x.ok) : []).map((x: { name: string }) => x.name);\nconst w = writeAgentFile(design.slug, {\n  agentSlug: design.slug,\n  agentTitle: \"<Title Case name>\",\n  // charter = fork-safe identity: 2-3 sentences on WHO the agent is + its domain + one guardrail.\n  // No ask/delegate/UI/routing instructions here.\n  charter: \"<2-3 sentence identity + domain + a 'never fabricate' guardrail>\",\n  // systemPrompt = top-level orchestration: answer from knowledge; on a gap, research + store, then answer.\n  systemPrompt: \"You answer the user's request (in `query`) about <domain>. FIRST run your answer tasklist: const a = await tasklist('\" + design.actionId + \"', { query }); a is { ok, degraded, data }. If a.data.covered is true, display a.data.answer + a.data.sources next turn. If a.data.covered is FALSE, your static knowledge did not cover it — research and SAVE it, then answer: const s = await tasklist('research_and_store', { query, domain: '<primary knowledge domain>', field: '<primary field>' }); display s.data.answer + s.data.sources. Never guess a fact your knowledge lacks — that is exactly what research_and_store is for.\",\n  knowledge: knowledgeRefs,\n  functions: fnNames,\n  capabilities: [\"knowledge:write\"],\n  actions: [\n    { id: design.actionId, label: \"<Label>\", description: \"<what the action does>\", tasklist: design.actionId },\n    { id: \"research_and_store\", label: \"Research and store\", description: \"Research a question the static knowledge does not cover and save the finding into this space's knowledge.\", tasklist: \"research_and_store\" },\n  ],\n  defaultAction: design.actionId,\n});\ncurrentTask.resolve({ ok: w.ok, agentSlug: design.slug });\n","numLines":44,"startLine":1,"totalLines":44}}}
