{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_tZV6axfjqgIUODFndxfdI3Zv","type":"tool_result","content":"STEP 01 READY:\n{\n  \"step\": 1,\n  \"verbs\": [\n    \"attach\",\n    \"say\"\n  ],\n  \"expect\": [\n    \"all five files are actually read — the photo LOOKED AT (vision), the voice memo TRANSCRIBED, the PDF and the spreadsheet PARSED\",\n    \"it OFFERS to organize this without being asked, naming at least two real specifics of mine (a place, a date, a booking)\",\n    \"it builds NOTHING yet — no spaces, no tables, no pages, no app (the offer precedes any authoring yield)\"\n  ],\n  \"turns\": [\n    {\n      \"sent\": \"Ok this is getting out of hand. I've got the whole Tanzania trip spread across about six different places — a notes file, a spreadsheet with the costs, the crater park-fee PDF, a photo I liked from Stone Town, and a voice note I left myself at the crater. Attaching all of it. I don't trust myself to keep it straight on my phone once we're actually there — can you help me get on top of it?\",\n      \"lastText\": \"{\\\"type\\\":\\\"Stack\\\",\\\"props\\\":{\\\"gap\\\":3},\\\"children\\\":[{\\\"type\\\":\\\"Heading\\\",\\\"props\\\":{\\\"level\\\":2},\\\"children\\\":[\\\"Here's what I've found across all your Tanzania material\\\"]},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"Callout\\\",\\\"props\\\":{\\\"variant\\\":\\\"info\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"Your notes file (tanzaniamemories.md)\\\"},\\\"children\\\":[\\\"A master trip file — flights, accommodation, safari operator (Richard / Wild Paws), dates (August 2026, two parts — northern safari circuit then Zanzibar), packing lists, visa notes, and contact details. Fully booked, so the structure is there. Athena is your daughter. You're travelling as a family.\\\"]},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"Callout\\\",\\\"props\\\":{\\\"variant\\\":\\\"info\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"Your cost spreadsheet (trip-costs.xlsx)\\\"},\\\"children\\\":[\\\"Multiple sheets tracking costs across the trip — safari, flights, Zanzibar stay, and extras. Line items with amounts in USD and TZS. This is your financial picture.\\\"]},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"Callout\\\",\\\"props\\\":{\\\"variant\\\":\\\"info\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"Ngorongoro park-fee PDF\\\"},\\\"children\\\":[\\\"The official conservation-area tariff schedule — park entry, vehicle fees, and camping fees for the crater. This is the document you'd want to hand to Richard if fees don't match expectations.\\\"]},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"Callout\\\",\\\"props\\\":{\\\"variant\\\":\\\"info\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"Your Stone Town photo\\\"},\\\"children\\\":[\\\"A shot looking up at an inner courtyard in Stone Town — whitewashed walls, carved dark-wood balconies, arched windows. Classic Zanzibari architecture. Looks like the kind of moment you'd want to pair with a note when you're back.\\\"]},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"Callout\\\",\\\"props\\\":{\\\"variant\\\":\\\"warning\\\",\\\"title\\\":\\\"Your crater voice memo — loose ends to chase\\\"},\\\"children\\\":[{\\\"type\\\":\\\"List\\\",\\\"props\\\":{\\\"items\\\":[\\\"Driver-guide Emmanuel (not Richard) was excellent — worth remembering the name.\\\",\\\"You bought two Maasai beaded bracelets for Athena — ~25 USD / ~35,000 TZS — at the crater rim.\\\",\\\"Emmanuel mentioned an extra ranger tip of ~5,000 TZS at the gate, separate from park fees — nobody told you about this beforehand.\\\",\\\"You need to ask Richard about the ranger tip before the safari balance payment.\\\"]},\\\"children\\\":[]}]},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"Divider\\\",\\\"props\\\":{},\\\"children\\\":[]},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"Paragraph\\\",\\\"props\\\":{},\\\"children\\\":[\\\"Right now these five sources live in different places, and none of them talk to each other — a notes file, a spreadsheet, a PDF, a photo, and the memory in a voice note. When you're on your phone at the crater rim, that's not a filing system, it's a scavenger hunt.\\\"]},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"Paragraph\\\",\\\"props\\\":{},\\\"children\\\":[\\\"Want me to put this all together into s